  "instructions": [
    "Heat a wok or large skillet with oil over medium heat.",
    "Add cashews, garlic, onions, green peppers, tomatoes, and optional soy sauce to the pan.",
    "Stir-fry until vegetables are slightly softened and cashews are lightly toasted, about 5 minutes.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together mirin, white wine vinegar, and water. Pour over stir-fried ingredients and toss to coat evenly.",
    "Cook for another minute or two until the sauce thickens slightly.",
    "Serve immediately as a side dish with your favorite noodles or rice."
